Original cred goes to zurb: http://www.zurb.com/article/982/a-new-take-on-responsive-tables

A jQuery plugin for dealing with large tables in small spaces.

Options and their defaults:

shrinkAt: 900
(the width of the window at which to convert the table into its alter ego)
tableClass: 'tiny-tables',
(the class added to the table that is targeted by the plugin)
tableWrapperClass: 'tiny-tables-wrap' ,
(the wrapper for the divs that are created)
scrollingClass: 'tiny-tables-scroll',
(the class for the div that contains the larger, x-scrollable table)
pinnedClass: 'tiny-tables-pinned'
(the class for the div that contains the first column of data)